posts.title: Fires from hell -- L. A.'s Pacific Palisades hit with 100 mph hot  winds -- it's all burning
posts.content:
The Pacific Palisades fire in L. A. is no joke. James Woods was on video and he began to weep. Over a thousand homes are burnt to the ground. And the fire departments are out of water. Some firefighters have died.

Those Santa Ana winds come swooping down into the bowl and dry things out...they're always hot and can reach 100 mph. They are horrible, terrifying. Winds from hell. You stand in front of a fan spraying putting water on yourself and it evaporates before it gets to you.

I wish a powerful deluge of rain would burst from the sky and extinguish all the fires--it's the only thing that can help now.

~ 08 January 2025
